The paper focuses on visual instance retrieval using ConvNets, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the performance of different image representations, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of ConvNets for image representation also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the challenge of constructing a tiny image representation, which could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
